# Design guidelines (scoped)

When these globs apply, treat **`@design-guidelines/OVERVIEW.md`** + **`@design-guidelines/INDEX.md`** + the relevant **`rules/**/*.mdc`** as **required context** (see also the always-on **`.cursor/rules/entry.mdc`** → *On every implementation or update*).

Do **not** duplicate token tables here — use the linked specs.

1. **`@design-guidelines/OVERVIEW.md`** — principles, tokens overview, layout, component index.
2. **`@design-guidelines/INDEX.md`** — pick the right `rules/**/*.mdc` for the surface (buttons, tables, sidebar, etc.).
3. **`@design-guidelines/README.md`** — onboarding when copying the pack to another repo.

Engineering refactors still follow **`@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md`**.

Project rule format (frontmatter, globs, rule types): [cursor.com/docs/rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules).
